.TH "HPC\-COMPOSE\-RUN" "1" "" "hpc\-compose 0.1.44" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hpc\-compose\-run \- Run a one\-off command in one service environment
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
hpc\-compose run [OPTIONS] <ARGS>...
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Submit a fresh one\-off job using either one service's image, environment, mounts, working directory, and prepare rules, or an ephemeral image supplied with \-\-image. Service mode uses: hpc\-compose run [\-f compose.yaml] SERVICE \-\- CMD. Image mode uses: hpc\-compose run \-\-image IMAGE [resources] \-\- CMD.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB-f\fR, \fB--file\fR \fIFILE\fR
Compose specification file to read; if omitted, use the active context compose file or fall back to compose.yaml.
.TP
\fIARGS\fR
Service plus command in service mode, or command argv in \-\-image mode.
.TP
\fB--image\fR \fIIMAGE\fR
Container image for ephemeral image mode.
.TP
\fB--resources\fR \fINAME\fR
Settings resource profile to apply in ephemeral image mode.
.TP
\fB--time\fR \fITIME\fR
Slurm time limit for ephemeral image mode.
.TP
\fB--mem\fR \fIMEM\fR
Slurm memory request for ephemeral image mode.
.TP
\fB--cpus\-per\-task\fR \fIN\fR
Slurm CPUs per task for ephemeral image mode.
.TP
\fB--gpus\fR \fIN\fR
Slurm GPU count for ephemeral image mode.
.TP
\fB--partition\fR \fIPARTITION\fR
Slurm partition for ephemeral image mode.
.TP
\fB--env\fR \fIKEY=VALUE\fR
Environment variable to pass into the ephemeral container.
.TP
\fB--local\fR
Run the ephemeral image locally through the local Pyxis\-compatible launcher.
.TP
\fB--script\-out\fR \fIOUTPUT\fR
Write the rendered launcher script to this path before submission.
.TP
\fB--sbatch\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the sbatch executable. Default: sbatch.
.TP
\fB--srun\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the srun executable. Default: srun.
.TP
\fB--enroot\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the enroot executable. Default: enroot.
.TP
\fB--apptainer\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the apptainer executable. Default: apptainer.
.TP
\fB--singularity\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the singularity executable. Default: singularity.
.TP
\fB--squeue\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the squeue executable. Default: squeue.
.TP
\fB--sacct\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the sacct executable. Default: sacct.
.TP
\fB--keep\-failed\-prep\fR
Keep failed preparation state on disk for later inspection.
.TP
\fB--skip\-prepare\fR
Skip image preparation and reuse existing artifacts.
.TP
\fB--force\-rebuild\fR
Refresh imported and prepared artifacts before submission.
.TP
\fB--no\-preflight\fR
Skip the preflight phase before submission.
.TP
\fB--color\fR \fIWHEN\fR
Controls colored output. Default: auto. Possible values: auto, always, never.
.TP
\fB--quiet\fR
Suppress progress indicators and non\-essential labels.
.TP
\fB--profile\fR \fINAME\fR
Profile name to load from .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB--settings\-file\fR \fIPATH\fR
Explicit settings file path; defaults to upward search for .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
Print help (see a summary with '\-h').
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
hpc\-compose run \-f compose.yaml app \-\- python \-m pytest
hpc\-compose run \-f compose.yaml app \-\- bash
hpc\-compose run \-\-image docker://python:3.12 \-\- python \-V
.fi
